CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1782145125
OL,3,CLandlords who refuse to fix dangerous
OL,4,Cproblems face fines of up to #7,000
OL,6,FThe new penalty sits alongside
OL,7,Fexisting powers councils can use,
OL,8,Fincluding forcing repairs, carrying
OL,9,Fout emergency works and recovering
OL,10,Fcosts from landlords who do not act.
OL,12,FHousing Secretary Steve Reed has
OL,13,Fwritten to mayors and is urging
OL,14,Fcouncils to use the powers at their
OL,15,Fdisposal to tackle unsafe housing.
OL,17,F"Renters deserve a safe, secure place
OL,18,Fto call home and our landmark Renters'
OL,19,FRights Act gives councils more options
OL,20,Fto take speedy action against rogue
OL,21,Flandlords.
OL,26,@yD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
